snippet.textDisplay:
Buy an Apex Pro or something Rhett, you shouldn't use such a crappy knife sharpener on such a nice Miyabi. Those carbide tooth style things usually aren't the right angle for a Japanese knife, and they are super rough on it. Theres heaps of nice fixed angle manual sharpeners that make using a proper stone easy as pie :)


I have the knife set below yours, they are pretty easy to go wrong with - I basically paid a guy to ruin the angle on mine and vowed to learn to sharpen it myself. Turns out that's hard, so just buy a fixed angle version, I learned the hard way so you don't have to!

Also never let link use your knives.
